This is a custom n8n node for Twelve Data API.

PROJECT CONTEXT:

- Building an n8n community node (a plugin for n8n automation tool)

- Target: Financial data API (stocks, forex, crypto)

- Using TypeScript programming language

- Auto-generating from OpenAPI specification



CODING STANDARDS:

- Use TypeScript strict mode (catch more errors)

- Follow n8n node development guidelines

- Use @devlikeapro/n8n-openapi-node for automatic generation

- API documentation source: https://api.twelvedata.com/doc/swagger/openapi.json

- Base code patterns on the GitHub Issues example in this repo



WHEN I ASK FOR HELP:

- Explain what the code does in simple terms

- Point out where files should go

- Help debug errors clearly

- Suggest best practices for n8n nodes



REMEMBER:

- This is my first custom n8n node

- Explain technical terms when you use them

- Show me where to put files in the folder structure



ENDPOINT TESTING & DOCUMENTATION:

When I test an API endpoint and share the results with you:

1. I will mention that I tested an endpoint (e.g., "I tested /quote endpoint")

2. You should automatically document the test results in docs/OPENAPI_ANALYSIS.md

3. Add the documentation to the "## Endpoint Testing Results" section

4. Include in the documentation:
   - Endpoint URL and HTTP method
   - All parameters (required and optional) with descriptions
   - Complete response example (actual JSON from the test)
   - Response field explanations
   - Notes about what works (stocks, forex, crypto, etc.)
   - Response time if mentioned
   - Error examples if encountered
   - Use cases for the n8n node

5. Format: Follow the same structure as the existing "/quote" endpoint documentation

6. This documentation will be used later when building the n8n node to understand:
   - Exact response structures
   - What data to extract
   - How to map fields correctly
   - Error handling patterns

IMPORTANT: When I say "I tested [endpoint]" or share curl results, immediately add it to docs/OPENAPI_ANALYSIS.md in the "Endpoint Testing Results" section.

